41 // __cpp_exceptions is referred from
42 // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/manual/using_exceptions.html
43 // gcc < 5 does not define __cpp_exceptions but __EXCEPTIONS,
44 // Microsoft C++ Compiler does not provide an option to disable exceptions
45 #ifndef DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
46 #if __cpp_exceptions || __EXCEPTIONS \
47  || (defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__))
48 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 1
49 #else
50 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 0
51 #endif
52 #endif
53 
54 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
55 #define DNNL_TRAP() __builtin_trap()
56 #elif defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
57 #define DNNL_TRAP() __debugbreak()
58 #else
59 #error "unknown compiler"
60 #endif
61 
62 #if DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
63 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) throw error(status, msg)
64 #else
65 #include <cstdio>
66 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) \
67  do { \
68  fputs(msg, stderr); \
69  DNNL_TRAP(); \
70  } while (0)
71 #endif

85 struct error : public std::exception {
86  dnnl_status_t status;
87  const char *message;
88 
93  error(dnnl_status_t astatus, const char *amessage)
94  : status(astatus), message(amessage) {}
95 
97  const char *what() const noexcept override { return message; }
98 
104  static void wrap_c_api(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message) {
105  if (status != dnnl_success) DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, message);
106  }
107 };
108 
110 template <typename T>
111 class handle_traits {};
112 
126 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
127 class handle {
128 private:
129  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
130 
131  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> _data {0};
132 
133 protected:
134  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == _data.get(); }
135  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
136 
137 public:
147  handle() = default;
148  handle(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
149  handle(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
150  handle<T, traits> &operator=(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
151  handle<T, traits> &operator=(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
152 
156  explicit handle(T t, bool weak = false) { reset(t, weak); }
157 
161  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
162  _data.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
163  }
164 
166  T get(bool allow_emtpy = false) const {
167  T result = _data.get();
168 
169  if (allow_emtpy == false && result == nullptr)
170  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
171  "attempt to use uninitialized object");
172  return result;
173  }
174 
177  explicit operator T() const { return get(true); }
178 
180  explicit operator bool() const { return get(true) != nullptr; }
181 
184  bool operator==(const handle &other) const {
185  return other._data.get() == _data.get();
186  }
187 
191  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
192 };

485 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
486  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
487  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
488  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
489  } \
490 \
491  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
492  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
493  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
494  } \
495 \
496  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
497  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
498  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
499  } \
500 \
501  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
502  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
503  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
504  return lhs; \
505  } \
506 \
507  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
508  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
509  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
510  return lhs; \
511  } \
512 \
513  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
514  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
515  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
516  return lhs; \
517  } \
518 \
519  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
520  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
521  }
522 
523 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(normalization_flags)
524 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(rnn_flags)
525 
526 #undef DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS

679  int len() const { return dnnl_post_ops_len(get()); }

682  primitive::kind kind(int index) const {
683  error::wrap_c_api(index < len() ? dnnl_success : dnnl_invalid_arguments,
684  "post_ops index is out of range");

686  dnnl_post_ops_get_kind(get(), index));

791  void get_output_scales(int &mask, std::vector<float> &scales) const {
792  dnnl_dim_t count;
793  int c_mask;
794  const float *c_scales;
795  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_get_output_scales(
796  get(), &count, &c_mask, &c_scales),
797  "could not get int output scales");
798  scales.resize(count);
799 
800  mask = c_mask;
801  for (dnnl_dim_t c = 0; c < count; ++c)
802  scales[c] = c_scales[c];
803  }
804 
820  void set_output_scales(int mask, const std::vector<float> &scales) {
821  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_set_output_scales(get(),
822  (dnnl_dim_t)scales.size(), mask, &scales[0]),
823  "could not set int output scales");
824  }
825 
827  const post_ops get_post_ops() const {
828  post_ops result;
829  const_dnnl_post_ops_t c_result;
830  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_get_post_ops(get(), &c_result),
831  "could not get post operation sequence");
832  result.reset(const_cast<dnnl_post_ops_t>(c_result), true);
833  return result;
834  }
835

839  "could not set post operation sequence");
840  }

902 struct engine : public handle<dnnl_engine_t> {

922  return dnnl_engine_get_count(convert_to_c(akind));
923  }
924 
931  engine(kind akind, size_t index) {

933  error::wrap_c_api(
934  dnnl_engine_create(&aengine, convert_to_c(akind), index),
935  "could not create an engine");

937  }
938 
939 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
940  engine(kind akind, cl_device_id device, cl_context context) {

944  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_create_ocl(&aengine, convert_to_c(akind),
945  device, context),
946  "could not create an engine");
947  reset(aengine);

954 
957  engine(const handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> &pd) {

960  dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
961  dnnl::convert_to_c(dnnl::query::engine), 0, &engine_q),
962  "could not get engine from primitive_desc");
963  reset(engine_q, true);
964  }

970  "could not get the engine kind");

972  }
973

979  "could not get a context handle");

981  }
982 
984  cl_device_id get_ocl_device() const {
985  cl_device_id device = nullptr;
986  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_device(get(), &device),
987  "could not get a device handle");
988  return device;
989  }
990 #endif
991 
994  template <class primitive_desc>
995  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd) {
996  return query(pd, dnnl::query::engine);
997  }
998 
999 private:
1001  static dnnl_engine_kind_t convert_to_c(kind akind) {
1002  return static_cast<dnnl_engine_kind_t>(akind);
1003  }
1004 
1005  template <class primitive_desc>
1006  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd, dnnl::query what) {
1007  dnnl_engine_t engine_q;
1008  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
1009  dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &engine_q),
1010  "could not get engine from primitive_desc");
1011  return engine(engine_q);
1012  }
1013 };

1024 template <>
1025 struct handle_traits<dnnl_stream_t> {
1026  static constexpr auto destructor = &dnnl_stream_destroy;
1027 };
1029 
1031 struct stream : public handle<dnnl_stream_t> {
1032  using handle::handle;
1033 
1035  enum class flags : unsigned {
1038  default_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1040  in_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1042  out_of_order = dnnl_stream_out_of_order,
1044  default_flags = dnnl_stream_default_flags,
1045  };
1046 
1047  stream() = default;
1048 
1051  stream(const engine &aengine, flags aflags = flags::default_flags) {
1052  dnnl_stream_t astream;
1053  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create(&astream, aengine.get(),
1054  static_cast<dnnl_stream_flags_t>(aflags)),
1055  "could not create a stream");
1056  reset(astream);
1057  }
1058 
1059 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1060  stream(const engine &eng, cl_command_queue queue) {
1063  dnnl_stream_t astream;
1064  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_ocl(&astream, eng.get(), queue),
1065  "could not create a stream");
1066  reset(astream);
1067  }
1068 
1070  cl_command_queue get_ocl_command_queue() const {
1071  cl_command_queue queue = nullptr;
1072  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_get_ocl_command_queue(get(), &queue),
1073  "could not get OpenCL command queue");
1074  return queue;
1075  }
1076 #endif
1077 
1079  stream &wait() {
1080  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_wait(get()), "could not wait a stream");
1081  return *this;
1082  }
1083 };
1084 
1085 inline stream::flags operator|(stream::flags lhs, stream::flags rhs) {
1086  return static_cast<stream::flags>(
1087  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs));
1088 }
1089 
1090 inline stream::flags operator&(stream::flags lhs, stream::flags rhs) {
1091  return static_cast<stream::flags>(
1092  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs));
1093 }
1094 
1095 inline stream::flags operator^(stream::flags lhs, stream::flags rhs) {
1096  return static_cast<stream::flags>(
1097  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs));
1098 }
1099 
1100 inline stream::flags operator~(stream::flags rhs) {
1101  return static_cast<stream::flags>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs));
1102 }

1469  struct desc {
1470  friend struct memory;
1472  dnnl_memory_desc_t data;
1473 
1475  desc() : data() {}
1476 
1482  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, format_tag aformat_tag) {
1483  validate_dims(adims);
1484  error::wrap_c_api(
1485  dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data, (int)adims.size(),
1486  adims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &adims[0],
1487  convert_to_c(adata_type),
1488  convert_to_c(aformat_tag)),
1489  "could not initialize a memory descriptor by tag");
1490  }
1491 
1497  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, const dims &astrides) {
1498  validate_dims(adims);
1499  error::wrap_c_api(
1500  dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data, (int)adims.size(),
1501  adims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &adims[0],
1502  convert_to_c(adata_type),
1503  astrides.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &astrides[0]),
1504  "could not initialize a memory descriptor by strides");
1505  }
1506 
1510  desc(const dnnl_memory_desc_t &adata) : data(adata) {}
1511 
1513  //
1516  desc submemory_desc(const dims &adims, const dims &offsets) {
1517  dnnl_memory_desc_t sub_md;
1518  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_desc_init_submemory(
1519  &sub_md, &data, &adims[0], &offsets[0]),
1520  "could not initialize a sub-memory");
1521  return desc(sub_md);
1522  }
1523 
1525  desc reshape(const dims &adims) {
1526  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md;
1527  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_desc_reshape(&out_md, &data,
1528  (int)adims.size(), &adims[0]),
1529  "could not reshape a memory descriptor");
1530  return desc(out_md);
1531  }
1532 
1535  size_t get_size() const { return dnnl_memory_desc_get_size(&data); }
1536 
1538  bool is_zero() const { return data.ndims == 0; }
1539 
1540  bool operator==(const desc &other) const {
1541  return dnnl_memory_desc_equal(&data, &other.data) != 0;
1542  }
1543 
1544  bool operator!=(const desc &other) const { return !operator==(other); }
1545  };

1557  dnnl_memory_create(&result, &md.data, aengine.get(), ahandle),
1558  "could not create a memory");
1559  reset(result);
1560  }

1566  memory(const desc &md, const engine &aengine)

1698 struct primitive_desc_base : public handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> {
1699  using handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t>::handle;
1700 
1701  primitive_desc_base() = default;
1702 
1704  engine get_engine() const { return engine::query(*this); }
1705 
1707  const char *impl_info_str() const {
1708  const char *res;
1709  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
1710  get(), dnnl_query_impl_info_str, 0, &res),
1711  "could not query implementation info string");
1712  return res;
1713  }
1714 
1716  memory::dim query_s64(query q) const {
1717  memory::dim res;
1718  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
1719  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(q), 0, &res);
1720  return status == dnnl_success ? res : 0;
1721  }
1722 
1724  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
1725  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
1726  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
1727  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md,
1728  query::exec_arg_md};
1729  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
1730  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
1731  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments, "invalid memory query");
1732 
1733  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
1734  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
1735  return memory::desc(*cdesc);
1736  }
1737 
1740  memory::desc src_desc(int idx) const {
1741  return query_md(query::src_md, idx);
1742  }
1743 
1746  memory::desc dst_desc(int idx) const {
1747  return query_md(query::dst_md, idx);
1748  }
1749 
1752  memory::desc weights_desc(int idx) const {
1753  return query_md(query::weights_md, idx);
1754  }
1755 
1758  memory::desc diff_src_desc(int idx) const {
1759  return query_md(query::diff_src_md, idx);
1760  }
1761 
1764  memory::desc diff_dst_desc(int idx) const {
1765  return query_md(query::diff_dst_md, idx);
1766  }
1767 
1770  memory::desc diff_weights_desc(int idx) const {
1771  return query_md(query::diff_weights_md, idx);
1772  }
1773 
1774  // Separate versions without the index argument for documentation
1775  // purposes.
1776 
1778  memory::desc src_desc() const { return src_desc(0); }
1779 
1781  memory::desc dst_desc() const { return dst_desc(0); }
1782 
1784  memory::desc weights_desc() const { return weights_desc(0); }
1785 
1787  memory::desc diff_src_desc() const { return diff_src_desc(0); }
1788 
1790  memory::desc diff_dst_desc() const { return diff_dst_desc(0); }
1791 
1793  memory::desc diff_weights_desc() const { return diff_weights_desc(0); }
1794 
1797  memory::desc workspace_desc() const {
1798  return query_md(query::workspace_md, 0);
1799  }
1800 
1803  memory::desc scratchpad_desc() const {
1804  return query_md(query::scratchpad_md, 0);
1805  }
1806 
1808  engine scratchpad_engine() const {
1809  dnnl_engine_t engine_q;
1810  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(get(),
1811  dnnl::convert_to_c(query::scratchpad_engine),
1812  0, &engine_q),
1813  "could not get scratchpad engine from a primitive_desc");
1814 
1815  return engine(engine_q);
1816  }
1817 
1819  primitive_attr get_primitive_attr() const {
1820  const_dnnl_primitive_attr_t const_cattr;
1821  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_get_attr(get(), &const_cattr),
1822  "could not get attributes");
1823  dnnl_primitive_attr_t cattr;
1824  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_clone(&cattr, const_cattr),
1825  "could not clone attributes");
1826 
1827  return primitive_attr(cattr);
1828  }
1829 
1830 protected:
1831  void reset_with_clone(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd) {
1832  dnnl_primitive_desc_t new_pd;
1833  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_clone(&new_pd, pd),
1834  "could not clone primitive descriptor");
1835  reset(new_pd);
1836  }
1837 
1838  primitive_desc_base(
1839  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind)
1840  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind::undef) {}
1841 
1842  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
1843  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind)
1844  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, prop_kind, prop_kind) {}
1845 
1852  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
1853  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1,
1854  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2) {
1855  // It is OK to pass an empty primitive descriptor
1856  if (pd == nullptr) return;
1857 
1858  dnnl_status_t rc;
1859 
1860  dnnl_primitive_kind_t c_prim_kind = convert_to_c(prim_kind);
1861  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
1862  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
1863 
1864  // Check that primitive kind matches
1865  dnnl_primitive_kind_t pd_kind;
1866  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
1867  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_kind);
1868  error::wrap_c_api(rc,
1869  "could not get primitive kind from the primitive descriptor");
1870  if (pd_kind != c_prim_kind)
1871  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
1872  "primitive descriptor operation kind mismatch");
1873 
1874  // Check that propagation kind matches
1875  dnnl_prop_kind_t pd_prop_kind;
1876  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
1877  pd, dnnl_query_prop_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_prop_kind);
1878 
1879  // Something went wrong
1880  if (rc != dnnl_success && rc != dnnl_unimplemented)
1881  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
1882  "could not get propagation kind "
1883  "from the primitive descriptor");
1884 
1885  // Everything is fine
1886  if ((rc == dnnl_unimplemented && c_prop_kind1 == dnnl_prop_kind_undef)
1887  || (rc == dnnl_success
1888  && (pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
1889  || pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind2))) {
1890  reset_with_clone(pd);
1891  return;
1892  }
1893 
1894  // We could get the propagation kind but there is a mismatch
1895  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
1896  "primitive descriptor propagation kind mismatch");
1897  }
1898 
1899 protected:
1900  using base = primitive_desc_base;
1901 };
1902

1906 
1909

1918 struct reorder : public primitive {
1920  struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
1921  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
1922 
1923  primitive_desc() = default;
1924 
1928  primitive_desc(const engine &src_engine, const memory::desc &src_md,
1929  const engine &dst_engine, const memory::desc &dst_md,
1930  const primitive_attr &aattr = primitive_attr()) {
1931  dnnl_primitive_desc_t result;
1932  error::wrap_c_api(
1933  dnnl_reorder_primitive_desc_create(&result, &src_md.data,
1934  src_engine.get(), &dst_md.data, dst_engine.get(),
1935  aattr.get()),
1936  "could not create a reorder primitive descriptor");
1937  reset(result);
1938  }
1939 
1943  primitive_desc(const memory &src, const memory &dst,
1944  const primitive_attr &aattr = primitive_attr()) {
1945  dnnl_primitive_desc_t result;
1946  auto src_md = src.get_desc();
1947  auto dst_md = dst.get_desc();
1948  error::wrap_c_api(
1949  dnnl_reorder_primitive_desc_create(&result, &src_md.data,
1950  src.get_engine().get(), &dst_md.data,
1951  dst.get_engine().get(), aattr.get()),
1952  "could not create a reorder primitive descriptor");
1953  reset(result);
1954  }
1955 
1958  primitive_desc(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd)
1959  : primitive_desc_base(pd, dnnl::primitive::kind::reorder) {}
1960 
1962  engine get_src_engine() const {
1963  return engine::query(*this, dnnl::query::reorder_src_engine);
1964  }
1965 
1967  engine get_dst_engine() const {
1968  return engine::query(*this, dnnl::query::reorder_dst_engine);
1969  }
1970 
1972  memory::desc src_desc() const { return base::src_desc(0); }
1973 
1975  memory::desc dst_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(0); }
1976  };
1977 
1978  reorder() = default;
1979 
1982  reorder(const primitive_desc &pd) : primitive(pd.get()) {}
1983 
1987  reorder(const memory &src, const memory &dst,
1988  const primitive_attr &aattr = primitive_attr())
1989  : primitive(primitive_desc(src, dst, aattr).get()) {}
1990 
1991  using primitive::execute;
1992 
1995  void execute(stream astream, memory &src, memory &dst) {
1996  primitive::execute(astream, {{DNNL_ARG_FROM, src}, {DNNL_ARG_TO, dst}});
1997  }
1998 };

2010 inline std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> convert_to_c(
2011  const std::vector<memory::desc> &mems) {
2012  std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> c_api_mems;
2013  c_api_mems.reserve(mems.size());
2014  for (const auto &s : mems)
2015  c_api_mems.push_back(s.data);
2016  return c_api_mems;
2017 }

2181 
2184 struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
2185  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
2186 
2187  primitive_desc() = default;
2188 
2194  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
2195  const engine &e, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd,
2196  bool allow_empty = false)
2197  : allow_empty(allow_empty) {
2198  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
2199  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
2200  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, e.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
2201  if (!allow_empty)
2202  error::wrap_c_api(
2203  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
2204  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
2205  fetch_impl();
2206  }
2207 
2214  bool next_impl() {
2215  dnnl_status_t status
2216  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
2217  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
2218  error::wrap_c_api(status, "primitive descriptor iterator next failed");
2219 
2220  fetch_impl();
2221  return true;
2222  }
2223 
2224 private:
2225  bool allow_empty = false;
2226  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
2227  void fetch_impl() {
2228  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
2229  pd_iterator.get(allow_empty));
2230  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr || allow_empty ? dnnl_success
2231  : dnnl_runtime_error,
2232  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from the iterator");
2233  reset(pd);
2234  }
2235 };

4475 struct rnn_primitive_desc_base : public primitive_desc {
4476  using primitive_desc::primitive_desc;
4477 
4478  rnn_primitive_desc_base() = default;
4479 
4482  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind,
4483  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind)
4484  : rnn_primitive_desc_base(pd, prop_kind, prop_kind, cell_kind) {}
4485 
4487  memory::desc src_layer_desc() const { return base::src_desc(0); }
4488 
4491  memory::desc src_iter_desc() const { return base::src_desc(1); }
4492 
4494  memory::desc src_iter_c_desc() const { return base::src_desc(2); }
4495 
4497  memory::desc weights_layer_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(0); }
4498 
4500  memory::desc weights_iter_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(1); }
4501 
4504  memory::desc bias_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(2); }
4505 
4507  memory::desc dst_layer_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(0); }
4508 
4511  memory::desc dst_iter_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(1); }
4512 
4514  memory::desc dst_iter_c_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(2); }
4515 
4517  memory::desc diff_src_layer_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(0); }
4518 
4521  memory::desc diff_src_iter_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(1); }
4522 
4524  memory::desc diff_src_iter_c_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(2); }
4525 
4527  memory::desc diff_weights_layer_desc() const {
4528  return base::diff_weights_desc(0);
4529  }
4530 
4532  memory::desc diff_weights_iter_desc() const {
4533  return base::diff_weights_desc(1);
4534  }
4535 
4537  memory::desc diff_bias_desc() const { return base::diff_weights_desc(2); }
4538 
4540  memory::desc diff_dst_layer_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(0); }
4541 
4544  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(1); }
4545 
4547  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_c_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(2); }
4548 
4549 protected:
4550  using rnn_base = rnn_primitive_desc_base;
4551 
4552  // Constructs an RNN primitive descriptor from a C counterpart while
4553  // checking that it actually describes the expected primitive.
4554  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
4555  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2,
4556  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind) {
4557  dnnl_rnn_desc_t *rnn_d;
4558  dnnl_status_t rc;
4559  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd, dnnl_query_rnn_d, 0, &rnn_d);
4560  error::wrap_c_api(
4561  rc, "could not retrieve rnn_desc from a primitive descriptor");
4562 
4563  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
4564  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
4565  dnnl_alg_kind_t c_cell_kind = convert_to_c(cell_kind);
4566 
4567  bool ok = rnn_d->primitive_kind == dnnl_rnn
4568  && (rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
4569  || rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind2)
4570  && rnn_d->cell_kind == c_cell_kind;
4571 
4572  if (!ok)
4573  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments, "rnn descriptor mismatch");
4574 
4575  reset_with_clone(pd);
4576  }
4577 };
4578 
4582 struct vanilla_rnn_forward : public primitive {
4583 
4585  struct desc {
4586  dnnl_rnn_desc_t data;
4587 
4606  desc(prop_kind aprop_kind, algorithm activation,
4607  rnn_direction direction, const memory::desc &src_layer_desc,
4608  const memory::desc &src_iter_desc,
4609  const memory::desc &weights_layer_desc,
4610  const memory::desc &weights_iter_desc,
4611  const memory::desc &bias_desc,
4612  const memory::desc &dst_layer_desc,
4613  const memory::desc &dst_iter_desc,
4614  rnn_flags flags = rnn_flags::undef, float alpha = 0.0f,

5953 inline void primitive::execute(
5954  stream &astream, const std::unordered_map<int, memory> &args) const {
5955  std::vector<dnnl_exec_arg_t> c_args;
5956  c_args.reserve(args.size());
5957  for (const auto &a : args)
5958  c_args.push_back({a.first, a.second.get()});
5959 
5960  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_execute(get(), astream.get(),
5961  (int)c_args.size(), c_args.data()),
5962  "could not execute a primitive");
5963 }
